[2026-05-19T00:54:04.303Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_function_4i8qtp5tn3zk_2","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Generating Mobile Screen Mockups (Flutter Target)\n2\t\n3\tThe complete workflow for generating a self-contained mobile screen mockup using the **Flutter HTML Glossary** vocabulary. Every mockup represents a single Flutter Scaffold — think of the HTML as a visual blueprint for the widget tree.\n4\t\n5\t**Input:** `.stitch/designs/{screenId}/SPEC.md` + `DESIGN.md` + matched example HTML\n6\t**Output:** `.stitch/designs/{screenId}/design.html`\n7\t\n8\t## Critical Rule\n9\t\n10\tAll HTML elements MUST use classes and `data-*` attributes from the **Flutter HTML Glossary** (`stitch-flutter/references/flutter-html-glossary.md`). This ensures pixel-perfect mechanical conversion to Flutter widgets.\n11\t\n12\t## Step 1: Analyze the Spec\n13\t\n14\tRead the SPEC.md and identify the mobile screen structure:\n15\t\n16\t1. **Scaffold chrome** — AppBar (title, leading, actions), BottomNavigationBar, FloatingActionButton\n17\t2. **Body structure** — scrollable content sections, SliverAppBar collapsing behavior, pull-to-refresh\n18\t3. **Data shape** — what entities are displayed, their fields and types\n19\t4. **Interaction states** — default, selected, loading (shimmer), empty, error\n20\t5. **Navigation targets** — which bottom tab is active, where card taps push to, what bottom sheets present\n21\t6. **Gestures** — swipe-to-dismiss, pull-to-refresh, long-press, horizontal scroll\n22\t\n23\tThis determines the screen pattern (Single Screen, Multi-State, or Celebration).\n24\t\n25\t## Step 2: Study the Matched Example\n26\t\n27\tRead the selected example's HTML file and note:\n28\t\n29\t- **Scaffold structure** — how AppBar, body, bottom nav, FAB are arranged\n30\t- **`:root` token block** — how design tokens are organized\n31\t- **Phone frame** — `.phone` wrapper (375x812pt, 40px radius)\n32\t- **Mobile patterns** — scroll behavior, card tap areas, horizontal carousels, bottom sheets\n33\t- **`data-flutter` usage** — which Flutter widgets are annotated\n34\t- **Animation approach** — `@keyframes` and `data-animate` for entry/exit transitions\n35\t- **State representation** — how loading, empty, selected states are shown\n36\t\n37\t## Step 3: Build the `:root` Block\n38\t\n39\tParse the DESIGN.md per `reading-design-md.md` and build the complete `:root` block. These tokens mirror the Flutter `AppTheme` constants — CSS makes the mockup look correct in a browser, while the `data-*` attributes encode the Flutter widget tree.\n40\t\n41\t```css\n42\t:root {\n43\t  /* ── Colors (map to ColorScheme) ── */\n44\t  --color-primary: #D4A520;\n45\t  --color-on-primary: #FFFFFF;\n46\t  --color-surface: #16213E;\n47\t  --color-on-surface: #E8E6E3;\n48\t  --color-background: #1A1A2E;\n49\t\n50\t  /* ── Typography (map to TextTheme via GoogleFonts) ── */\n51\t  --font-primary: 'Outfit', sans-serif;\n52\t\n53\t  /* ── Spacing (map to AppTheme constants) ── */\n54\t  --space-xs: 4px;\n55\t  --space-sm: 8px;\n56\t  --space-md: 16px;\n57\t  --space-lg: 24px;\n58\t\n59\t  /* ── Radius (map to AppTheme.radiusX) ── */\n60\t  --radius-sm: 8px;\n61\t  --radius-md: 12px;\n62\t  --radius-lg: 16px;\n63\t\n64\t  /* ── Motion (map to AppTheme curves/durations) ── */\n65\t  --ease-bounce: cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.56, 0.64, 1);\n66\t  --duration-fast: 150ms;\n67\t  --duration-normal: 250ms;\n68\t}\n69\t```\n70\t\n71\t## Step 4: Build the HTML Document\n72\t\n73\t```html\n74\t<!DOCTYPE html>\n75\t<html lang=\"en\">\n76\t<head>\n77\t  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n78\t  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=375, initial-scale=1.0\" />\n79\t  <title>{Screen Name} — Design</title>\n80\t  <link rel=\"preconnect\" href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com\" />\n81\t  <link href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Outfit:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap\" rel=\"stylesheet\" />\n82\t  <style>\n83\t    *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }\n84\t\n85\t    :root { /* tokens */ }\n86\t\n87\t    body {\n88\t      font-family: var(--font-primary);\n89\t      background: #E8E8E8;\n90\t      display: flex;\n91\t      justify-content: center;\n92\t      padding: 32px 16px;\n93\t      min-height: 100vh;\n94\t    }\n95\t\n96\t    .phone {\n97\t      width: 375px;\n98\t      min-height: 812px;\n99\t      background: var(--color-background);\n100\t      border-radius: 40px;\n101\t      overflow: hidden;\n102\t      position: relative;\n103\t      box-shadow: 0 24px 64px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);\n104\t    }\n105\t\n106\t    /* ── Glossary element styling ── */\n107\t    /* CSS here makes the glossary elements LOOK correct in browser */\n108\t    /* The converter reads data-* attributes, not CSS */\n109\t\n110\t    .scaffold { display: flex; flex-direction: column; min-height: 100%; }\n111\t    .app-bar { display: flex; align-items: center; height: 56px; padding: 0 var(--space-sm); }\n112\t    .body { flex: 1; overflow-y: auto; }\n113\t    .bottom-nav { display: flex; justify-content: space-around; height: 56px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); }\n114\t\n115\t    .column { display: flex; flex-direction: column; }\n116\t    .row { display: flex; flex-direction: row; align-items: center; }\n117\t    .center { display: flex; justify-content: center; align-items: center; }\n118\t    .expanded { flex: 1; }\n119\t    .wrap { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; }\n120\t\n121\t    /* ... more glossary element styles ... */\n122\t\n123\t    @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {\n124\t      *, *::before, *::after {\n125\t        animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;\n126\t        transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;\n127\t      }\n128\t    }\n129\t  </style>\n130\t</head>\n131\t<body>\n132\t  <div class=\"phone\">\n133\t    <div class=\"scaffold\">\n134\t      <header class=\"app-bar\" data-color=\"surface\">\n135\t        <div class=\"app-bar__title\">\n136\t          <span class=\"title-large\" data-color=\"on-surface\">{Title}</span>\n137\t        </div>\n138\t      </header>\n139\t      <main class=\"body\">\n140\t        <!-- Glossary elements only -->\n141\t      </main>\n142\t      <nav class=\"bottom-nav\" data-color=\"surface\">\n143\t        <!-- bottom-nav__item elements -->\n144\t      </nav>\n145\t    </div>\n146\t  </div>\n147\t</body>\n148\t</html>\n149\t```\n150\t\n151\t## Step 5: Use ONLY Glossary Elements\n152\t\n153\tWhen building the screen content:\n154\t\n155\t### For a card list:\n156\t```html\n157\t<div class=\"list-view\" data-separator=\"false\">\n158\t  <div class=\"ink-well\" data-route=\"/novel/1\">\n159\t    <div class=\"card\" data-radius=\"md\" data-elevation=\"1\">\n160\t      <div class=\"padding\" data-p=\"md\">\n161\t        <div class=\"row\" data-spacing=\"md\">\n162\t          <div class=\"clip-rrect\" data-radius=\"sm\">\n163\t            <img class=\"network-image\" data-src=\"https://picsum.photos/seed/n1/100/150\" data-w=\"80\" data-h=\"120\" />\n164\t          </div>\n165\t          <div class=\"column expanded\" data-spacing=\"xs\">\n166\t            <span class=\"title-medium\" data-color=\"on-surface\">The Dragon's Apprentice</span>\n167\t            <span class=\"body-small\" data-color=\"on-surface-variant\">Sarah Chen</span>\n168\t            <div class=\"row\" data-spacing=\"xs\">\n169\t              <svg class=\"icon\" data-name=\"star\" data-size=\"16\" data-color=\"primary\"></svg>\n170\t              <span class=\"label-small\" data-color=\"on-surface-variant\">4.8</span>\n171\t            </div>\n172\t          </div>\n173\t          <svg class=\"icon\" data-name=\"chevron_right\" data-size=\"24\" data-color=\"on-surface-variant\"></svg>\n174\t        </div>\n175\t      </div>\n176\t    </div>\n177\t  </div>\n178\t</div>\n179\t```\n180\t\n181\t### For a horizontal scroll section:\n182\t```html\n183\t<div class=\"column\" data-spacing=\"sm\">\n184\t  <div class=\"padding\" data-px=\"md\">\n185\t    <div class=\"row\" data-main-axis=\"space-between\">\n186\t      <span class=\"title-medium\" data-color=\"on-surface\">Trending Now</span>\n187\t      <button class=\"text-btn\">See All</button>\n188\t    </div>\n189\t  </div>\n190\t  <div class=\"horizontal-scroll\">\n191\t    <div class=\"row\" data-spacing=\"sm\">\n192\t      <div class=\"padding\" data-pl=\"md\">\n193\t        <div class=\"ink-well\" data-route=\"/novel/1\">\n194\t          <!-- card content -->\n195\t        </div>\n196\t      </div>\n197\t      <!-- more items -->\n198\t    </div>\n199\t  </div>\n200\t</div>\n201\t```\n202\t\n203\t### For filter chips:\n204\t```html\n205\t<div class=\"horizontal-scroll\">\n206\t  <div class=\"row\" data-spacing=\"sm\">\n207\t    <div class=\"padding\" data-pl=\"md\">\n208\t      <div class=\"filter-chip\" data-label=\"All\" data-selected=\"true\"></div>\n209\t    </div>\n210\t    <div class=\"filter-chip\" data-label=\"Fantasy\" data-selected=\"false\"></div>\n211\t    <div class=\"filter-chip\" data-label=\"Sci-Fi\" data-selected=\"false\"></div>\n212\t    <div class=\"filter-chip\" data-label=\"Romance\" data-selected=\"false\"></div>\n213\t  </div>\n214\t</div>\n215\t```\n216\t\n217\t## Step 6: CSS Styling for Browser Preview\n218\t\n219\tThe CSS makes the mockup look like a real mobile app in the browser. Style each glossary class to match the Flutter design system. The converter **ignores CSS** — it reads only HTML structure + `data-*` attributes.\n220\t\n221\t```css\n222\t/* Cards */\n223\t.card {\n224\t  background: var(--color-surface);\n225\t  border-radius: var(--radius-md);\n226\t  box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);\n227\t}\n228\t\n229\t/* Buttons */\n230\t.elevated-btn {\n231\t  background: var(--color-primary);\n232\t  color: var(--color-on-primary);\n233\t  border-radius: var(--radius-sm);\n234\t  padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md);\n235\t  font-weight: 600;\n236\t  border: none;\n237\t  cursor: pointer;\n238\t  min-height: 44px;\n239\t}\n240\t\n241\t/* Text styles */\n242\t.title-large { font-size: 22px; font-weight: 600; }\n243\t.title-medium { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 500; }\n244\t.body-large { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; }\n245\t.body-medium { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 400; }\n246\t.body-small { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 400; }\n247\t.label-small { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 500; }\n248\t```\n249\t\n250\t## Step 7: Animations\n251\t\n252\tDefine `@keyframes` in CSS for browser preview, and encode with `data-animate` for Flutter conversion:\n253\t\n254\t```html\n255\t<!-- Element with animation -->\n256\t<div class=\"card\" data-animate=\"fade-in\" data-animate-delay=\"0\" data-animate-duration=\"300\">\n257\t```\n258\t\n259\t```css\n260\t/* Browser preview animation */\n261\t@keyframes fade-in {\n262\t  from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(8px); }\n263\t  to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }\n264\t}\n265\t[data-animate=\"fade-in\"] {\n266\t  animation: fade-in var(--duration-normal) var(--ease-out) backwards;\n267\t}\n268\t[data-animate-delay=\"100\"] { animation-delay: 100ms; }\n269\t[data-animate-delay=\"200\"] { animation-delay: 200ms; }\n270\t```\n271\t\n272\t## Step 8: Mobile Accessibility\n273\t\n274\t| Requirement | Implementation |\n275\t|---|---|\n276\t| Touch targets | `min-height: 48px` on all tappable elements (Material 3 minimum) |\n277\t| Interactive elements labeled | `aria-label=\"Close\"` on icon buttons → `Semantics()` in Flutter |\n278\t| Active tab indicated | `data-selected=\"true\"` on active nav destination |\n279\t| Navigation landmarks | `<nav class=\"bottom-nav\">` → `NavigationBar` |\n280\t| Decorative content hidden | `aria-hidden=\"true\"` on decorative icons → `excludeSemantics` |\n281\t| Reduced motion | `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` → `MediaQuery.disableAnimations` |\n282\t| Heading hierarchy | Typography classes in logical order → `Semantics(header: true)` |\n283\t| Thumb reachability | Primary actions in bottom half of screen |\n284\t\n285\t## Cross-Reference\n286\t\n287\t- Token extraction: `reading-design-md.md`\n288\t- Example selection: `selecting-examples.md`\n289\t- Glossary: `stitch-flutter/references/flutter-html-glossary.md`\n290\t- Conversion: `stitch-flutter/SKILL.md`\n291\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ffadc2ab-9d56-40d7-9c22-5f10b583dc26","uuid":"2225c64e-9766-47ca-94a5-10d5580679d7","timestamp":"2026-05-19T00:54:04.302Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/minh/Documents/openplayboosks/examples/baby-app/.converge/skills/stitch-generate/references/generating-html-screens.md","content":"# Generating Mobile Screen Mockups (Flutter Target)\n\nThe complete workflow for generating a self-contained mobile screen mockup using the **Flutter HTML Glossary** vocabulary. Every mockup represents a single Flutter Scaffold — think of the HTML as a visual blueprint for the widget tree.\n\n**Input:** `.stitch/designs/{screenId}/SPEC.md` + `DESIGN.md` + matched example HTML\n**Output:** `.stitch/designs/{screenId}/design.html`\n\n## Critical Rule\n\nAll HTML elements MUST use classes and `data-*` attributes from the **Flutter HTML Glossary** (`stitch-flutter/references/flutter-html-glossary.md`). This ensures pixel-perfect mechanical conversion to Flutter widgets.\n\n## Step 1: Analyze the Spec\n\nRead the SPEC.md and identify the mobile screen structure:\n\n1. **Scaffold chrome** — AppBar (title, leading, actions), BottomNavigationBar, FloatingActionButton\n2. **Body structure** — scrollable content sections, SliverAppBar collapsing behavior, pull-to-refresh\n3. **Data shape** — what entities are displayed, their fields and types\n4. **Interaction states** — default, selected, loading (shimmer), empty, error\n5. **Navigation targets** — which bottom tab is active, where card taps push to, what bottom sheets present\n6. **Gestures** — swipe-to-dismiss, pull-to-refresh, long-press, horizontal scroll\n\nThis determines the screen pattern (Single Screen, Multi-State, or Celebration).\n\n## Step 2: Study the Matched Example\n\nRead the selected example's HTML file and note:\n\n- **Scaffold structure** — how AppBar, body, bottom nav, FAB are arranged\n- **`:root` token block** — how design tokens are organized\n- **Phone frame** — `.phone` wrapper (375x812pt, 40px radius)\n- **Mobile patterns** — scroll behavior, card tap areas, horizontal carousels, bottom sheets\n- **`data-flutter` usage** — which Flutter widgets are annotated\n- **Animation approach** — `@keyframes` and `data-animate` for entry/exit transitions\n- **State representation** — how loading, empty, selected states are shown\n\n## Step 3: Build the `:root` Block\n\nParse the DESIGN.md per `reading-design-md.md` and build the complete `:root` block. These tokens mirror the Flutter `AppTheme` constants — CSS makes the mockup look correct in a browser, while the `data-*` attributes encode the Flutter widget tree.\n\n```css\n:root {\n  /* ── Colors (map to ColorScheme) ── */\n  --color-primary: #D4A520;\n  --color-on-primary: #FFFFFF;\n  --color-surface: #16213E;\n  --color-on-surface: #E8E6E3;\n  --color-background: #1A1A2E;\n\n  /* ── Typography (map to TextTheme via GoogleFonts) ── */\n  --font-primary: 'Outfit', sans-serif;\n\n  /* ── Spacing (map to AppTheme constants) ── */\n  --space-xs: 4px;\n  --space-sm: 8px;\n  --space-md: 16px;\n  --space-lg: 24px;\n\n  /* ── Radius (map to AppTheme.radiusX) ── */\n  --radius-sm: 8px;\n  --radius-md: 12px;\n  --radius-lg: 16px;\n\n  /* ── Motion (map to AppTheme curves/durations) ── */\n  --ease-bounce: cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.56, 0.64, 1);\n  --duration-fast: 150ms;\n  --duration-normal: 250ms;\n}\n```\n\n## Step 4: Build the HTML Document\n\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=375, initial-scale=1.0\" />\n  <title>{Screen Name} — Design</title>\n  <link rel=\"preconnect\" href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com\" />\n  <link href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Outfit:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap\" rel=\"stylesheet\" />\n  <style>\n    *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }\n\n    :root { /* tokens */ }\n\n    body {\n      font-family: var(--font-primary);\n      background: #E8E8E8;\n      display: flex;\n      justify-content: center;\n      padding: 32px 16px;\n      min-height: 100vh;\n    }\n\n    .phone {\n      width: 375px;\n      min-height: 812px;\n      background: var(--color-background);\n      border-radius: 40px;\n      overflow: hidden;\n      position: relative;\n      box-shadow: 0 24px 64px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);\n    }\n\n    /* ── Glossary element styling ── */\n    /* CSS here makes the glossary elements LOOK correct in browser */\n    /* The converter reads data-* attributes, not CSS */\n\n    .scaffold { display: flex; flex-direction: column; min-height: 100%; }\n    .app-bar { display: flex; align-items: center; height: 56px; padding: 0 var(--space-sm); }\n    .body { flex: 1; overflow-y: auto; }\n    .bottom-nav { display: flex; justify-content: space-around; height: 56px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); }\n\n    .column { display: flex; flex-direction: column; }\n    .row { display: flex; flex-direction: row; align-items: center; }\n    .center { display: flex; justify-content: center; align-items: center; }\n    .expanded { flex: 1; }\n    .wrap { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; }\n\n    /* ... more glossary element styles ... */\n\n    @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {\n      *, *::before, *::after {\n        animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;\n        transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;\n      }\n    }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <div class=\"phone\">\n    <div class=\"scaffold\">\n      <header class=\"app-bar\" data-color=\"surface\">\n        <div class=\"app-bar__title\">\n          <span class=\"title-large\" data-color=\"on-surface\">{Title}</span>\n        </div>\n      </header>\n      <main class=\"body\">\n        <!-- Glossary elements only -->\n      </main>\n      <nav class=\"bottom-nav\" data-color=\"surface\">\n        <!-- bottom-nav__item elements -->\n      </nav>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\n## Step 5: Use ONLY Glossary Elements\n\nWhen building the screen content:\n\n### For a card list:\n```html\n<div class=\"list-view\" data-separator=\"false\">\n  <div class=\"ink-well\" data-route=\"/novel/1\">\n    <div class=\"card\" data-radius=\"md\" data-elevation=\"1\">\n      <div class=\"padding\" data-p=\"md\">\n        <div class=\"row\" data-spacing=\"md\">\n          <div class=\"clip-rrect\" data-radius=\"sm\">\n            <img class=\"network-image\" data-src=\"https://picsum.photos/seed/n1/100/150\" data-w=\"80\" data-h=\"120\" />\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"column expanded\" data-spacing=\"xs\">\n            <span class=\"title-medium\" data-color=\"on-surface\">The Dragon's Apprentice</span>\n            <span class=\"body-small\" data-color=\"on-surface-variant\">Sarah Chen</span>\n            <div class=\"row\" data-spacing=\"xs\">\n              <svg class=\"icon\" data-name=\"star\" data-size=\"16\" data-color=\"primary\"></svg>\n              <span class=\"label-small\" data-color=\"on-surface-variant\">4.8</span>\n            </div>\n          </div>\n          <svg class=\"icon\" data-name=\"chevron_right\" data-size=\"24\" data-color=\"on-surface-variant\"></svg>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n```\n\n### For a horizontal scroll section:\n```html\n<div class=\"column\" data-spacing=\"sm\">\n  <div class=\"padding\" data-px=\"md\">\n    <div class=\"row\" data-main-axis=\"space-between\">\n      <span class=\"title-medium\" data-color=\"on-surface\">Trending Now</span>\n      <button class=\"text-btn\">See All</button>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"horizontal-scroll\">\n    <div class=\"row\" data-spacing=\"sm\">\n      <div class=\"padding\" data-pl=\"md\">\n        <div class=\"ink-well\" data-route=\"/novel/1\">\n          <!-- card content -->\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      <!-- more items -->\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n```\n\n### For filter chips:\n```html\n<div class=\"horizontal-scroll\">\n  <div class=\"row\" data-spacing=\"sm\">\n    <div class=\"padding\" data-pl=\"md\">\n      <div class=\"filter-chip\" data-label=\"All\" data-selected=\"true\"></div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"filter-chip\" data-label=\"Fantasy\" data-selected=\"false\"></div>\n    <div class=\"filter-chip\" data-label=\"Sci-Fi\" data-selected=\"false\"></div>\n    <div class=\"filter-chip\" data-label=\"Romance\" data-selected=\"false\"></div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n```\n\n## Step 6: CSS Styling for Browser Preview\n\nThe CSS makes the mockup look like a real mobile app in the browser. Style each glossary class to match the Flutter design system. The converter **ignores CSS** — it reads only HTML structure + `data-*` attributes.\n\n```css\n/* Cards */\n.card {\n  background: var(--color-surface);\n  border-radius: var(--radius-md);\n  box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);\n}\n\n/* Buttons */\n.elevated-btn {\n  background: var(--color-primary);\n  color: var(--color-on-primary);\n  border-radius: var(--radius-sm);\n  padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md);\n  font-weight: 600;\n  border: none;\n  cursor: pointer;\n  min-height: 44px;\n}\n\n/* Text styles */\n.title-large { font-size: 22px; font-weight: 600; }\n.title-medium { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 500; }\n.body-large { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; }\n.body-medium { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 400; }\n.body-small { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 400; }\n.label-small { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 500; }\n```\n\n## Step 7: Animations\n\nDefine `@keyframes` in CSS for browser preview, and encode with `data-animate` for Flutter conversion:\n\n```html\n<!-- Element with animation -->\n<div class=\"card\" data-animate=\"fade-in\" data-animate-delay=\"0\" data-animate-duration=\"300\">\n```\n\n```css\n/* Browser preview animation */\n@keyframes fade-in {\n  from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(8px); }\n  to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }\n}\n[data-animate=\"fade-in\"] {\n  animation: fade-in var(--duration-normal) var(--ease-out) backwards;\n}\n[data-animate-delay=\"100\"] { animation-delay: 100ms; }\n[data-animate-delay=\"200\"] { animation-delay: 200ms; }\n```\n\n## Step 8: Mobile Accessibility\n\n| Requirement | Implementation |\n|---|---|\n| Touch targets | `min-height: 48px` on all tappable elements (Material 3 minimum) |\n| Interactive elements labeled | `aria-label=\"Close\"` on icon buttons → `Semantics()` in Flutter |\n| Active tab indicated | `data-selected=\"true\"` on active nav destination |\n| Navigation landmarks | `<nav class=\"bottom-nav\">` → `NavigationBar` |\n| Decorative content hidden | `aria-hidden=\"true\"` on decorative icons → `excludeSemantics` |\n| Reduced motion | `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` → `MediaQuery.disableAnimations` |\n| Heading hierarchy | Typography classes in logical order → `Semantics(header: true)` |\n| Thumb reachability | Primary actions in bottom half of screen |\n\n## Cross-Reference\n\n- Token extraction: `reading-design-md.md`\n- Example selection: `selecting-examples.md`\n- Glossary: `stitch-flutter/references/flutter-html-glossary.md`\n- Conversion: `stitch-flutter/SKILL.md`\n","numLines":291,"startLine":1,"totalLines":291}}}
[2026-05-19T00:54:04.303Z] [STREAM_EVENT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_function_4i8qtp5tn3zk_2","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Generating Mobile Screen Mockups (Flutter Target)\n2\t\n3\tThe complete workflow for generating a self-contained mobile screen mockup using the **Flutter HTML Glossary** vocabulary. Every mockup represents a single Flutter Scaffold — think of the HTML as a visual blueprint for the widget tree.\n4\t\n5\t**Input:** `.stitch/designs/{screenId}/SPEC.md` + `DESIGN.md` + matched example HTML\n6\t**Output:** `.stitch/designs/{screenId}/design.html`\n7\t\n8\t## Critical Rule\n9\t\n10\tAll HTML elements MUST use classes and `data-*` attributes from the **Flutter HTML Glossary** (`stitch-flutter/references/flutter-html-glossary.md`). This ensures pixel-perfect mechanical conversion to Flutter widgets.\n11\t\n12\t## Step 1: Analyze the Spec\n13\t\n14\tRead the SPEC.md and identify the mobile screen structure:\n15\t\n16\t1. **Scaffold chrome** — AppBar (title, leading, actions), BottomNavigationBar, FloatingActionButton\n17\t2. **Body structure** — scrollable content sections, SliverAppBar collapsing behavior, pull-to-refresh\n18\t3. **Data shape** — what entities are displayed, their fields and types\n19\t4. **Interaction states** — default, selected, loading (shimmer), empty, error\n20\t5. **Navigation targets** — which bottom tab is active, where card taps push to, what bottom sheets present\n21\t6. **Gestures** — swipe-to-dismiss, pull-to-refresh, long-press, horizontal scroll\n22\t\n23\tThis determines the screen pattern (Single Screen, Multi-State, or Celebration).\n24\t\n25\t## Step 2: Study the Matched Example\n26\t\n27\tRead the selected example's HTML file and note:\n28\t\n29\t- **Scaffold structure** — how AppBar, body, bottom nav, FAB are arranged\n30\t- **`:root` token block** — how design tokens are organized\n31\t- **Phone frame** — `.phone` wrapper (375x812pt, 40px radius)\n32\t- **Mobile patterns** — scroll behavior, card tap areas, horizontal carousels, bottom sheets\n33\t- **`data-flutter` usage** — which Flutter widgets are annotated\n34\t- **Animation approach** — `@keyframes` and `data-animate` for entry/exit transitions\n35\t- **State representation** — how loading, empty, selected states are shown\n36\t\n37\t## Step 3: Build the `:root` Block\n38\t\n39\tParse the DESIGN.md per `reading-design-md.md` and build the complete `:root` block. These tokens mirror the Flutter `AppTheme` constants — CSS makes the mockup look correct in a browser, while the `data-*` attributes encode the Flutter widget tree.\n40\t\n41\t```css\n42\t:root {\n43\t  /* ── Colors (map to ColorScheme) ── */\n44\t  --color-primary: #D4A520;\n45\t  --color-on-primary: #FFFFFF;\n46\t  --color-surface: #16213E;\n47\t  --color-on-surface: #E8E6E3;\n48\t  --color-background: #1A1A2E;\n49\t\n50\t  /* ── Typography (map to TextTheme via GoogleFonts) ── */\n51\t  --font-primary: 'Outfit', sans-serif;\n52\t\n53\t  /* ── Spacing (map to AppTheme constants) ── */\n54\t  --space-xs: 4px;\n55\t  --space-sm: 8px;\n56\t  --space-md: 16px;\n57\t  --space-lg: 24px;\n58\t\n59\t  /* ── Radius (map to AppTheme.radiusX) ── */\n60\t  --radius-sm: 8px;\n61\t  --radius-md: 12px;\n62\t  --radius-lg: 16px;\n63\t\n64\t  /* ── Motion (map to AppTheme curves/durations) ── */\n65\t  --ease-bounce: cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.56, 0.64, 1);\n66\t  --duration-fast: 150ms;\n67\t  --duration-normal: 250ms;\n68\t}\n69\t```\n70\t\n71\t## Step 4: Build the HTML Document\n72\t\n73\t```html\n74\t<!DOCTYPE html>\n75\t<html lang=\"en\">\n76\t<head>\n77\t  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n78\t  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=375, initial-scale=1.0\" />\n79\t  <title>{Screen Name} — Design</title>\n80\t  <link rel=\"preconnect\" href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com\" />\n81\t  <link href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Outfit:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap\" rel=\"stylesheet\" />\n82\t  <style>\n83\t    *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }\n84\t\n85\t    :root { /* tokens */ }\n86\t\n87\t    body {\n88\t      font-family: var(--font-primary);\n89\t      background: #E8E8E8;\n90\t      display: flex;\n91\t      justify-content: center;\n92\t      padding: 32px 16px;\n93\t      min-height: 100vh;\n94\t    }\n95\t\n96\t    .phone {\n97\t      width: 375px;\n98\t      min-height: 812px;\n99\t      background: var(--color-background);\n100\t      border-radius: 40px;\n101\t      overflow: hidden;\n102\t      position: relative;\n103\t      box-shadow: 0 24px 64px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);\n104\t    }\n105\t\n106\t    /* ── Glossary element styling ── */\n107\t    /* CSS here makes the glossary elements LOOK correct in browser */\n108\t    /* The converter reads data-* attributes, not CSS */\n109\t\n110\t    .scaffold { display: flex; flex-direction: column; min-height: 100%; }\n111\t    .app-bar { display: flex; align-items: center; height: 56px; padding: 0 var(--space-sm); }\n112\t    .body { flex: 1; overflow-y: auto; }\n113\t    .bottom-nav { display: flex; justify-content: space-around; height: 56px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); }\n114\t\n115\t    .column { display: flex; flex-direction: column; }\n116\t    .row { display: flex; flex-direction: row; align-items: center; }\n117\t    .center { display: flex; justify-content: center; align-items: center; }\n118\t    .expanded { flex: 1; }\n119\t    .wrap { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; }\n120\t\n121\t    /* ... more glossary element styles ... */\n122\t\n123\t    @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {\n124\t      *, *::before, *::after {\n125\t        animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;\n126\t        transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;\n127\t      }\n128\t    }\n129\t  </style>\n130\t</head>\n131\t<body>\n132\t  <div class=\"phone\">\n133\t    <div class=\"scaffold\">\n134\t      <header class=\"app-bar\" data-color=\"surface\">\n135\t        <div class=\"app-bar__title\">\n136\t          <span class=\"title-large\" data-color=\"on-surface\">{Title}</span>\n137\t        </div>\n138\t      </header>\n139\t      <main class=\"body\">\n140\t        <!-- Glossary elements only -->\n141\t      </main>\n142\t      <nav class=\"bottom-nav\" data-color=\"surface\">\n143\t        <!-- bottom-nav__item elements -->\n144\t      </nav>\n145\t    </div>\n146\t  </div>\n147\t</body>\n148\t</html>\n149\t```\n150\t\n151\t## Step 5: Use ONLY Glossary Elements\n152\t\n153\tWhen building the screen content:\n154\t\n155\t### For a card list:\n156\t```html\n157\t<div class=\"list-view\" data-separator=\"false\">\n158\t  <div class=\"ink-well\" data-route=\"/novel/1\">\n159\t    <div class=\"card\" data-radius=\"md\" data-elevation=\"1\">\n160\t      <div class=\"padding\" data-p=\"md\">\n161\t        <div class=\"row\" data-spacing=\"md\">\n162\t          <div class=\"clip-rrect\" data-radius=\"sm\">\n163\t            <img class=\"network-image\" data-src=\"https://picsum.photos/seed/n1/100/150\" data-w=\"80\" data-h=\"120\" />\n164\t          </div>\n165\t          <div class=\"column expanded\" data-spacing=\"xs\">\n166\t            <span class=\"title-medium\" data-color=\"on-surface\">The Dragon's Apprentice</span>\n167\t            <span class=\"body-small\" data-color=\"on-surface-variant\">Sarah Chen</span>\n168\t            <div class=\"row\" data-spacing=\"xs\">\n169\t              <svg class=\"icon\" data-name=\"star\" data-size=\"16\" data-color=\"primary\"></svg>\n170\t              <span class=\"label-small\" data-color=\"on-surface-variant\">4.8</span>\n171\t            </div>\n172\t          </div>\n173\t          <svg class=\"icon\" data-name=\"chevron_right\" data-size=\"24\" data-color=\"on-surface-variant\"></svg>\n174\t        </div>\n175\t      </div>\n176\t    </div>\n177\t  </div>\n178\t</div>\n179\t```\n180\t\n181\t### For a horizontal scroll section:\n182\t```html\n183\t<div class=\"column\" data-spacing=\"sm\">\n184\t  <div class=\"padding\" data-px=\"md\">\n185\t    <div class=\"row\" data-main-axis=\"space-between\">\n186\t      <span class=\"title-medium\" data-color=\"on-surface\">Trending Now</span>\n187\t      <button class=\"text-btn\">See All</button>\n188\t    </div>\n189\t  </div>\n190\t  <div class=\"horizontal-scroll\">\n191\t    <div class=\"row\" data-spacing=\"sm\">\n192\t      <div class=\"padding\" data-pl=\"md\">\n193\t        <div class=\"ink-well\" data-route=\"/novel/1\">\n194\t          <!-- card content -->\n195\t        </div>\n196\t      </div>\n197\t      <!-- more items -->\n198\t    </div>\n199\t  </div>\n200\t</div>\n201\t```\n202\t\n203\t### For filter chips:\n204\t```html\n205\t<div class=\"horizontal-scroll\">\n206\t  <div class=\"row\" data-spacing=\"sm\">\n207\t    <div class=\"padding\" data-pl=\"md\">\n208\t      <div class=\"filter-chip\" data-label=\"All\" data-selected=\"true\"></div>\n209\t    </div>\n210\t    <div class=\"filter-chip\" data-label=\"Fantasy\" data-selected=\"false\"></div>\n211\t    <div class=\"filter-chip\" data-label=\"Sci-Fi\" data-selected=\"false\"></div>\n212\t    <div class=\"filter-chip\" data-label=\"Romance\" data-selected=\"false\"></div>\n213\t  </div>\n214\t</div>\n215\t```\n216\t\n217\t## Step 6: CSS Styling for Browser Preview\n218\t\n219\tThe CSS makes the mockup look like a real mobile app in the browser. Style each glossary class to match the Flutter design system. The converter **ignores CSS** — it reads only HTML structure + `data-*` attributes.\n220\t\n221\t```css\n222\t/* Cards */\n223\t.card {\n224\t  background: var(--color-surface);\n225\t  border-radius: var(--radius-md);\n226\t  box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);\n227\t}\n228\t\n229\t/* Buttons */\n230\t.elevated-btn {\n231\t  background: var(--color-primary);\n232\t  color: var(--color-on-primary);\n233\t  border-radius: var(--radius-sm);\n234\t  padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md);\n235\t  font-weight: 600;\n236\t  border: none;\n237\t  cursor: pointer;\n238\t  min-height: 44px;\n239\t}\n240\t\n241\t/* Text styles */\n242\t.title-large { font-size: 22px; font-weight: 600; }\n243\t.title-medium { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 500; }\n244\t.body-large { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; }\n245\t.body-medium { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 400; }\n246\t.body-small { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 400; }\n247\t.label-small { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 500; }\n248\t```\n249\t\n250\t## Step 7: Animations\n251\t\n252\tDefine `@keyframes` in CSS for browser preview, and encode with `data-animate` for Flutter conversion:\n253\t\n254\t```html\n255\t<!-- Element with animation -->\n256\t<div class=\"card\" data-animate=\"fade-in\" data-animate-delay=\"0\" data-animate-duration=\"300\">\n257\t```\n258\t\n259\t```css\n260\t/* Browser preview animation */\n261\t@keyframes fade-in {\n262\t  from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(8px); }\n263\t  to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }\n264\t}\n265\t[data-animate=\"fade-in\"] {\n266\t  animation: fade-in var(--duration-normal) var(--ease-out) backwards;\n267\t}\n268\t[data-animate-delay=\"100\"] { animation-delay: 100ms; }\n269\t[data-animate-delay=\"200\"] { animation-delay: 200ms; }\n270\t```\n271\t\n272\t## Step 8: Mobile Accessibility\n273\t\n274\t| Requirement | Implementation |\n275\t|---|---|\n276\t| Touch targets | `min-height: 48px` on all tappable elements (Material 3 minimum) |\n277\t| Interactive elements labeled | `aria-label=\"Close\"` on icon buttons → `Semantics()` in Flutter |\n278\t| Active tab indicated | `data-selected=\"true\"` on active nav destination |\n279\t| Navigation landmarks | `<nav class=\"bottom-nav\">` → `NavigationBar` |\n280\t| Decorative content hidden | `aria-hidden=\"true\"` on decorative icons → `excludeSemantics` |\n281\t| Reduced motion | `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` → `MediaQuery.disableAnimations` |\n282\t| Heading hierarchy | Typography classes in logical order → `Semantics(header: true)` |\n283\t| Thumb reachability | Primary actions in bottom half of screen |\n284\t\n285\t## Cross-Reference\n286\t\n287\t- Token extraction: `reading-design-md.md`\n288\t- Example selection: `selecting-examples.md`\n289\t- Glossary: `stitch-flutter/references/flutter-html-glossary.md`\n290\t- Conversion: `stitch-flutter/SKILL.md`\n291\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ffadc2ab-9d56-40d7-9c22-5f10b583dc26","uuid":"2225c64e-9766-47ca-94a5-10d5580679d7","timestamp":"2026-05-19T00:54:04.302Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/minh/Documents/openplayboosks/examples/baby-app/.converge/skills/stitch-generate/references/generating-html-screens.md","content":"# Generating Mobile Screen Mockups (Flutter Target)\n\nThe complete workflow for generating a self-contained mobile screen mockup using the **Flutter HTML Glossary** vocabulary. Every mockup represents a single Flutter Scaffold — think of the HTML as a visual blueprint for the widget tree.\n\n**Input:** `.stitch/designs/{screenId}/SPEC.md` + `DESIGN.md` + matched example HTML\n**Output:** `.stitch/designs/{screenId}/design.html`\n\n## Critical Rule\n\nAll HTML elements MUST use classes and `data-*` attributes from the **Flutter HTML Glossary** (`stitch-flutter/references/flutter-html-glossary.md`). This ensures pixel-perfect mechanical conversion to Flutter widgets.\n\n## Step 1: Analyze the Spec\n\nRead the SPEC.md and identify the mobile screen structure:\n\n1. **Scaffold chrome** — AppBar (title, leading, actions), BottomNavigationBar, FloatingActionButton\n2. **Body structure** — scrollable content sections, SliverAppBar collapsing behavior, pull-to-refresh\n3. **Data shape** — what entities are displayed, their fields and types\n4. **Interaction states** — default, selected, loading (shimmer), empty, error\n5. **Navigation targets** — which bottom tab is active, where card taps push to, what bottom sheets present\n6. **Gestures** — swipe-to-dismiss, pull-to-refresh, long-press, horizontal scroll\n\nThis determines the screen pattern (Single Screen, Multi-State, or Celebration).\n\n## Step 2: Study the Matched Example\n\nRead the selected example's HTML file and note:\n\n- **Scaffold structure** — how AppBar, body, bottom nav, FAB are arranged\n- **`:root` token block** — how design tokens are organized\n- **Phone frame** — `.phone` wrapper (375x812pt, 40px radius)\n- **Mobile patterns** — scroll behavior, card tap areas, horizontal carousels, bottom sheets\n- **`data-flutter` usage** — which Flutter widgets are annotated\n- **Animation approach** — `@keyframes` and `data-animate` for entry/exit transitions\n- **State representation** — how loading, empty, selected states are shown\n\n## Step 3: Build the `:root` Block\n\nParse the DESIGN.md per `reading-design-md.md` and build the complete `:root` block. These tokens mirror the Flutter `AppTheme` constants — CSS makes the mockup look correct in a browser, while the `data-*` attributes encode the Flutter widget tree.\n\n```css\n:root {\n  /* ── Colors (map to ColorScheme) ── */\n  --color-primary: #D4A520;\n  --color-on-primary: #FFFFFF;\n  --color-surface: #16213E;\n  --color-on-surface: #E8E6E3;\n  --color-background: #1A1A2E;\n\n  /* ── Typography (map to TextTheme via GoogleFonts) ── */\n  --font-primary: 'Outfit', sans-serif;\n\n  /* ── Spacing (map to AppTheme constants) ── */\n  --space-xs: 4px;\n  --space-sm: 8px;\n  --space-md: 16px;\n  --space-lg: 24px;\n\n  /* ── Radius (map to AppTheme.radiusX) ── */\n  --radius-sm: 8px;\n  --radius-md: 12px;\n  --radius-lg: 16px;\n\n  /* ── Motion (map to AppTheme curves/durations) ── */\n  --ease-bounce: cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.56, 0.64, 1);\n  --duration-fast: 150ms;\n  --duration-normal: 250ms;\n}\n```\n\n## Step 4: Build the HTML Document\n\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=375, initial-scale=1.0\" />\n  <title>{Screen Name} — Design</title>\n  <link rel=\"preconnect\" href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com\" />\n  <link href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Outfit:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap\" rel=\"stylesheet\" />\n  <style>\n    *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }\n\n    :root { /* tokens */ }\n\n    body {\n      font-family: var(--font-primary);\n      background: #E8E8E8;\n      display: flex;\n      justify-content: center;\n      padding: 32px 16px;\n      min-height: 100vh;\n    }\n\n    .phone {\n      width: 375px;\n      min-height: 812px;\n      background: var(--color-background);\n      border-radius: 40px;\n      overflow: hidden;\n      position: relative;\n      box-shadow: 0 24px 64px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);\n    }\n\n    /* ── Glossary element styling ── */\n    /* CSS here makes the glossary elements LOOK correct in browser */\n    /* The converter reads data-* attributes, not CSS */\n\n    .scaffold { display: flex; flex-direction: column; min-height: 100%; }\n    .app-bar { display: flex; align-items: center; height: 56px; padding: 0 var(--space-sm); }\n    .body { flex: 1; overflow-y: auto; }\n    .bottom-nav { display: flex; justify-content: space-around; height: 56px; border-top: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); }\n\n    .column { display: flex; flex-direction: column; }\n    .row { display: flex; flex-direction: row; align-items: center; }\n    .center { display: flex; justify-content: center; align-items: center; }\n    .expanded { flex: 1; }\n    .wrap { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; }\n\n    /* ... more glossary element styles ... */\n\n    @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {\n      *, *::before, *::after {\n        animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;\n        transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;\n      }\n    }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <div class=\"phone\">\n    <div class=\"scaffold\">\n      <header class=\"app-bar\" data-color=\"surface\">\n        <div class=\"app-bar__title\">\n          <span class=\"title-large\" data-color=\"on-surface\">{Title}</span>\n        </div>\n      </header>\n      <main class=\"body\">\n        <!-- Glossary elements only -->\n      </main>\n      <nav class=\"bottom-nav\" data-color=\"surface\">\n        <!-- bottom-nav__item elements -->\n      </nav>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\n## Step 5: Use ONLY Glossary Elements\n\nWhen building the screen content:\n\n### For a card list:\n```html\n<div class=\"list-view\" data-separator=\"false\">\n  <div class=\"ink-well\" data-route=\"/novel/1\">\n    <div class=\"card\" data-radius=\"md\" data-elevation=\"1\">\n      <div class=\"padding\" data-p=\"md\">\n        <div class=\"row\" data-spacing=\"md\">\n          <div class=\"clip-rrect\" data-radius=\"sm\">\n            <img class=\"network-image\" data-src=\"https://picsum.photos/seed/n1/100/150\" data-w=\"80\" data-h=\"120\" />\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"column expanded\" data-spacing=\"xs\">\n            <span class=\"title-medium\" data-color=\"on-surface\">The Dragon's Apprentice</span>\n            <span class=\"body-small\" data-color=\"on-surface-variant\">Sarah Chen</span>\n            <div class=\"row\" data-spacing=\"xs\">\n              <svg class=\"icon\" data-name=\"star\" data-size=\"16\" data-color=\"primary\"></svg>\n              <span class=\"label-small\" data-color=\"on-surface-variant\">4.8</span>\n            </div>\n          </div>\n          <svg class=\"icon\" data-name=\"chevron_right\" data-size=\"24\" data-color=\"on-surface-variant\"></svg>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n```\n\n### For a horizontal scroll section:\n```html\n<div class=\"column\" data-spacing=\"sm\">\n  <div class=\"padding\" data-px=\"md\">\n    <div class=\"row\" data-main-axis=\"space-between\">\n      <span class=\"title-medium\" data-color=\"on-surface\">Trending Now</span>\n      <button class=\"text-btn\">See All</button>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"horizontal-scroll\">\n    <div class=\"row\" data-spacing=\"sm\">\n      <div class=\"padding\" data-pl=\"md\">\n        <div class=\"ink-well\" data-route=\"/novel/1\">\n          <!-- card content -->\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      <!-- more items -->\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n```\n\n### For filter chips:\n```html\n<div class=\"horizontal-scroll\">\n  <div class=\"row\" data-spacing=\"sm\">\n    <div class=\"padding\" data-pl=\"md\">\n      <div class=\"filter-chip\" data-label=\"All\" data-selected=\"true\"></div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"filter-chip\" data-label=\"Fantasy\" data-selected=\"false\"></div>\n    <div class=\"filter-chip\" data-label=\"Sci-Fi\" data-selected=\"false\"></div>\n    <div class=\"filter-chip\" data-label=\"Romance\" data-selected=\"false\"></div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n```\n\n## Step 6: CSS Styling for Browser Preview\n\nThe CSS makes the mockup look like a real mobile app in the browser. Style each glossary class to match the Flutter design system. The converter **ignores CSS** — it reads only HTML structure + `data-*` attributes.\n\n```css\n/* Cards */\n.card {\n  background: var(--color-surface);\n  border-radius: var(--radius-md);\n  box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);\n}\n\n/* Buttons */\n.elevated-btn {\n  background: var(--color-primary);\n  color: var(--color-on-primary);\n  border-radius: var(--radius-sm);\n  padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md);\n  font-weight: 600;\n  border: none;\n  cursor: pointer;\n  min-height: 44px;\n}\n\n/* Text styles */\n.title-large { font-size: 22px; font-weight: 600; }\n.title-medium { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 500; }\n.body-large { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 400; }\n.body-medium { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 400; }\n.body-small { font-size: 12px; font-weight: 400; }\n.label-small { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 500; }\n```\n\n## Step 7: Animations\n\nDefine `@keyframes` in CSS for browser preview, and encode with `data-animate` for Flutter conversion:\n\n```html\n<!-- Element with animation -->\n<div class=\"card\" data-animate=\"fade-in\" data-animate-delay=\"0\" data-animate-duration=\"300\">\n```\n\n```css\n/* Browser preview animation */\n@keyframes fade-in {\n  from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(8px); }\n  to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }\n}\n[data-animate=\"fade-in\"] {\n  animation: fade-in var(--duration-normal) var(--ease-out) backwards;\n}\n[data-animate-delay=\"100\"] { animation-delay: 100ms; }\n[data-animate-delay=\"200\"] { animation-delay: 200ms; }\n```\n\n## Step 8: Mobile Accessibility\n\n| Requirement | Implementation |\n|---|---|\n| Touch targets | `min-height: 48px` on all tappable elements (Material 3 minimum) |\n| Interactive elements labeled | `aria-label=\"Close\"` on icon buttons → `Semantics()` in Flutter |\n| Active tab indicated | `data-selected=\"true\"` on active nav destination |\n| Navigation landmarks | `<nav class=\"bottom-nav\">` → `NavigationBar` |\n| Decorative content hidden | `aria-hidden=\"true\"` on decorative icons → `excludeSemantics` |\n| Reduced motion | `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)` → `MediaQuery.disableAnimations` |\n| Heading hierarchy | Typography classes in logical order → `Semantics(header: true)` |\n| Thumb reachability | Primary actions in bottom half of screen |\n\n## Cross-Reference\n\n- Token extraction: `reading-design-md.md`\n- Example selection: `selecting-examples.md`\n- Glossary: `stitch-flutter/references/flutter-html-glossary.md`\n- Conversion: `stitch-flutter/SKILL.md`\n","numLines":291,"startLine":1,"totalLines":291}}}
[2026-05-19T00:54:04.304Z] [TOOL_RESULT] 1	# Generating Mobile Screen Mockups (Flutter Target)
2	
3	The complete workflow for generating a self-contained mobile screen mockup using the **Flutter HTML Glossary** vocabulary. Every mockup represents a single Flutter Scaffold — think of the HTML as a visual blueprint for the widget tree.
4	
5	**Input:** `.stitch/designs/{screenId}/SPEC.md` + `DESIGN.md` + matched example HTML
6	**Output:** `.stitch/designs/{screenId}/design.html`
7	
8	## Critical Rule
9	
10	All HTML elements MUST use classes and `data-*` attributes from the **Flutter HTML Glossary** (`stitch-flutter/references/flutter-html-glossary.md`). This ensures pixel-perfect mechanical conversion to Flutter widgets.
11	
12	## Step 1: Analyze the Spec
13	
14	Read the SPEC.md and identify the mobile screen structure:
15	
16	1. **Scaffold chrome** — AppBar (title, leading, actions), BottomNavigationBar, FloatingActionButton
17	2. **Body structure** — scrollable content sections, SliverAppBar collapsing behavior, pull-to-refresh
18	3. **Data shape** — what entities are displayed, their fields and types
19	4. **Interaction states** — default, selected, loading (shimmer), empty, error
20	5. **Navigation targets** — which bottom tab is active, where card taps push to, what bottom sheets present
21	6. **Gestures** — swipe-to-dismiss, pull-to-refresh, long-press, horizontal scroll
22	
23	This determines the screen pattern (Single Screen, Multi-State, or Celebration).
